Go ahead. Ask him about his hair.

46
00:04:01,014 --> 00:04:04,214
He suffered third degree burns
over 54% of his body a year ago

47
00:04:04,224 --> 00:04:06,958
and arrived in the ER last
night disoriented and shivering.

48
00:04:06,959 --> 00:04:10,163
For 12 hours his temperature
was bouncing between 96 and 102.

49
00:04:10,287 --> 00:04:12,574
Why don't you contest the
search of the pharmacy records?

50
00:04:12,575 --> 00:04:15,464
Yeah, you could argue it violated
doctor-patient confidentiality.

51
00:04:15,465 --> 00:04:17,192
Except he wasn't the
patient or the doctor.

52
00:04:17,193 --> 00:04:20,143
He was the guy who stole
from the patient and the doctor.

53
00:04:20,239 --> 00:04:23,061
This was the third time he had
been disoriented in the last two weeks.

54
00:04:23,062 --> 00:04:26,662
Running into smoke-filled burning
buildings can be a bit disorienting.

55
00:04:27,528 --> 00:04:29,951
Fortunately, I have the cure.
Stop doing it.

56
00:04:29,952 --> 00:04:32,567
He's not in a burning building anymore,
and he's still shivering.

57
00:04:32,568 --> 00:04:35,184
A hypothalamic tumor could
cause a vacillating temperature.

58
00:04:35,185 --> 00:04:37,852
So could ER nurses who are
too busy to notice that a patient likes

59
00:04:37,853 --> 00:04:39,766
both hot coffee and cold sodas.

60
00:04:43,252 --> 00:04:46,952
He tested negative for Hep C, TB,
HIV, Lyme, and his tox screen's clean.

61
00:04:50,872 --> 00:04:53,474
In case you hadn't noticed,
not exactly in the mood to dance.

62
00:04:53,475 --> 00:04:56,425
